Pasco — Marvin Marvin is a 6-year-old male dog of unknown breed. He’s friendly and loves to snuggle and give kisses. He’s eager to make friends, but tends to be rambunctious at times. He’s sure to make you laugh as he runs around the yard with the “zoomies.” Marvin walks well on a leash and knows the sit and down commands. For more information, call Pasco County Animal Services at 813-929-1212. Hernando — Allie Allie is a female terrier mix of unknown age. She loves spending time playing with her toys and shelter volunteers. She enjoys going for long walks and is working on basic commands. Allie will be spayed, microchipped and vaccinated upon adoption. For more information, call Hernando County Animal Services at 352-796-5062. Manatee — Hollywood Hollywood is a 1-year-old male mixed breed dog. He is shy around people. Once he warms up to you, he loves to cuddle and adores affection. He enjoys playing fetch with his toys. Hollywood walks well on a leash. For more information, e-mail adoptions@mymanatee.org. Pinellas — Ebony and Ember Ebony is a black female cat that isn’t quite 1 year old. Ember is a 4-month-old tortoiseshell kitten. This mother-daughter pair is shy and best suited for a quiet home without children. Their current foster family does not require they be adopted together, but it would be nice. For more information, call Save Our Strays at 727-545-1116. Hillsborough — Lady Lady is a 4-month-old female Catahoula Leopard and Cur Hound mix. She like cats, but prefers the strength and stamina of other dogs. She enjoys playing and romping with her toys. Lady is friendly, active, intelligent and crate trained. She will grow to be a high-end medium-size dog and requires a fenced yard. For more information, e-mail ourpawprinthearts@gmail.com.